Overall, I'm loving this watch!

      Ive been using the Spade & Co Health Smartwatch 4 for a while now, and its actually better than I thought.

      The battery life is just great, I have gone 8 days without charging, which is a nice change from my old Apple Watch that barely make it through 1 day.

      The screen is bright and easy to read, even outside in the sun. Its responsive, looks sharp, and doesnt feel laggy like some other budget smartwatch I had to return.

      I took it for a few runs alongside an old Garmin forerunner and the mileage was pretty much the same.

      I wasnt thrilled with the veryfit app at first but I have gotten used to it and mostly just sync up with Apple health and use that to check my stats. By the way, I see other reviews saying the app charged them but it wasnt my experience, its completely free.

      Is it an Apple Watch? No, but its much cheaper, looks good and does what I need. Will probably buy one for my kids!
